# Build the soul store and graft renderer

## Step

Resolved when `~/.brain/resources/soul/principles.svx` exists in
dark-wizard with the capped structure (principle, why, receipts,
last-validated, admitted-at), a renderer turns it into
`scripts/fleet/soul.block.md`, `fleet-graft.sh install` injects the
`soul` marker block into STEERING prompt surfaces only (per decision 1:
Claude/codex/pi steering files, NOT worker briefs), and the cap (~20)
is enforced by the renderer (it fails loudly if the store exceeds cap).
An empty-but-wired soul block shipping fleet-wide counts as done;
content arrives via the gate.
